---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="White Papers | Neurobotics">
  <div class="page-wrapper">
    
    <!-- SECTION 1: TWO COLUMN HERO BLOCK -->
    <section class="content-card two-column">
      
      <!-- Left Side: Image -->
      <div class="media-col">
        <img src="/assets/images/vector-graphic-edited.png" alt="Neurobotics Abstract Hardware" class="responsive-image" />
      </div>
      
      <!-- Right Side: Text & Video Knockout -->
      <div class="text-col align-center">
        <h1 class="main-title">The White Papers</h1>
        <hr class="title-divider" />
        <h2 class="subtitle">Sovereign Architecture & Verifiable Physics</h2>
        <br>
        <p>At Neurobotics, we believe that mission-critical autonomy must be mathematically verifiable, physically auditable, and structurally sovereign. True cognitive security demands absolute transparency in mathematics and total sovereignty in execution. We engineer austere, zero-fail autonomy built on rigorous physics and deterministic bare-metal architectures—not the probabilistic black boxes of the cloud.</p>
        <br>
        <p>Neurobotics has pioneered an entirely new paradigm: Deterministic Autonomy. This approach grounds cognition in auditable mathematics and biomimetic principles, ensuring absolute predictability, radically lower power consumption, and instantaneous response times without external dependencies. This repository serves as the unclassified intelligence archive for the Silicon-Based Artificial Life Form (SBALF) framework. It houses the foundational physics research authored by our Chief Science Officer, the architectural blueprints for our deterministic neuroanatomy, and the raw, unmodified telemetry logs from our hardware deployments.</p>
        <br>
        <p>By maintaining this direct-release repository, we bypass academic bottlenecks and ensure our mathematical proofs, field observations, and architectural briefings enter the operational record immediately. This establishes undeniable provenance and allows for rapid operational evaluation by the defense, aerospace, and deep-tech communities. As our R&D cycle advances, new artifacts will be added. All documents below are secure, unedited exports straight from the bench—presented exactly as they were engineered.
        <!-- Video Text Knockout Wrapper -->
        <div class="video-text-knockout">
          <video autoplay loop muted playsinline>
            <!-- Set this to your newly renamed video file! -->
            <source src="/assets/videos/gold-parkle-water-2.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          </video>
          <h2 class="knockout-heading">ESSE QUAM VIDERI</h2>
        </div>
        
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 2: PUBLICATIONS BUTTONS BLOCK -->
    <section class="publications-section">
      <h3 class="publications-title">Current Publications:</h3>
      
      <div class="button-grid">
        <!-- Row 1 -->
        <a href="/assets/docs/death-of-the-data-center-paper.pdf" class="pub-button" target="_blank">THE DEATH OF THE DATA CENTERS</a>
        <a href="/assets/docs/renshaw-theory-paper.pdf" class="pub-button" target="_blank">THE RENSHAW THEORY</a>
        <a href="/assets/docs/slaying-heisenbergs-dragon-rescuing-shrodingers-cat-paper.pdf" class="pub-button" target="_blank">HOW TO RESCUE SCHRÖDINGER'S CAT AND SLAY HEISENBERG'S DRAGON</a>
        
        <!-- Row 2 -->
        <a href="/assets/docs/llm-is-brocas-area-paper.pdf" class="pub-button" target="_blank">THE LLM AS BROCA'S AREA - IT'S NOT THE ENTIRE BRAIN</a>
        <a href="/assets/docs/renshaw-observation-paper.pdf" class="pub-button" target="_blank">THE RENSHAW OBSERVATION THEORY</a>
        <a href="/assets/docs/bubo-adam-eve-sbalf-paper.pdf" class="pub-button" target="_blank">BUBO ADAM & EVE SILICON BASED ARTIFICIAL LIFEFORMS (SBALF)</a>
        
        <!-- Row 3 (Grid handles this automatically!) -->
        <a href="/assets/docs/peanutpi-console-log-adam-sbalf.pdf" class="pub-button" target="_blank">BUBO ADAM & EVE SBALF CONSOLE LOGS PROOF</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div> <!-- Closes .page-wrapper -->

  <style>
    /* --- 1. BASE PAGE LAYOUT --- */
    .page-wrapper {
      background-color: #050a15; 
      padding: 60px 20px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 60px; 
    }

    .content-card {
      background-color: #000000;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 1200px;
      border-radius: 8px; 
      overflow: hidden; 
    }

    .padded-card {
      padding: 60px;
    }

    /* --- 2. TOP ROW: TWO COLUMN --- */
    .two-column {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .media-col {
      height: 100%;
    }

    .responsive-image {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover; /* Perfectly crops the image to fill the half-card! */
      display: block; 
    }

    .text-col {
      color: #e0e0e0;
      line-height: 1.6;
      padding: 60px; 
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center; 
    }

    .align-center {
      text-align: left;
    }

    /* Typography */
    .main-title {
      font-size: 3rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #ffffff;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    .title-divider {
      width: 100%;
      border: 0;
      border-top: 1px solid #4a5c73;
      margin: 0 0 20px 0; 
    }

    .subtitle {
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      font-weight: 300;
      color: #cccccc;
      margin-top: 0;
    }

/* --- 3. MOTTO TEXT (Dynamic Video Knockout) --- */
    .video-text-knockout {
      position: relative;
      margin-top: 40px;
      width: 100%;
      height: 120px; /* Increased from 80px to give it plenty of vertical breathing room */
      overflow: hidden;
      background-color: #000000; 
    }

    .video-text-knockout video {
      position: absolute;
      top: 50%;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translate(-50%, -50%); 
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
    }

    .knockout-heading {
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      margin: 0;
      
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center; 
      
      font-size: 2.2rem; /* Slightly smaller (down from 2.8rem) so it flows better */
      line-height: 1.3;  /* Controls spacing between lines if it wraps */
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      
      /* THE MAGIC LAYER */
/* Changed from #000000 to perfectly match your page background */
background-color: #050a15; 
color: #ffffff;
mix-blend-mode: multiply;
    }

    /* Mobile Responsiveness */
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .video-text-knockout {
        height: 100px;
      }
      .knockout-heading {
        font-size: 1.8rem; 
        justify-content: center; 
      }
    }

/* --- 4. BOTTOM ROW: PUBLICATIONS --- */
    .publications-section {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 35px;
      margin-top: 50px; /* Gives the whole publications area breathing room from the hero block */
      margin-bottom: 60px; /* Keeps it spaced nicely away from the footer logo */
      
      /* --- THE NEW BOUNDARIES --- */
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 1200px; /* Stops the grid from stretching infinitely */
      margin-left: auto; /* Pushes inward from the left */
      margin-right: auto; /* Pushes inward from the right (centering it!) */
      padding: 0 20px; /* Gives the sides a little breathing room on small screens */
    }
    /* --- TITLE STYLING --- */
    .publications-section h3 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;   /* Adjust this number up or down to dial in the perfect size */
      font-weight: 800;    /* 400 is normal, 700 is bold, 800/900 is extra bold */
      color: #ffffff;      /* Keeps it crisp and white */
    }

    .button-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(350px, 1fr));
      gap: 20px;
    }

    /* We use the "!important" tag on color to force the browser to override any old white text rules */
    .pub-button {
      background-color: #0b111e; 
      color: #00e5ff !important; /* Forces the crisp engineering Cyan to display! */
      border: 1px solid #203554; 
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 30px 20px;        /* Added extra top/bottom padding so the boxes feel spacious */
      font-size: 0.85rem; 
      font-weight: 600;
      text-align: center;
      text-decoration: none;
      line-height: 1.6;
      transition: all 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.8, 0.25, 1);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 100px;         /* Raised min-height slightly so long text has plenty of air */
    }

    .pub-button:hover {
      background-color: #111a2e;
      border-color: #d4af37;     
      color: #ffffff !important; /* Snaps to crisp white on hover over the gold box aura */
      box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.18); 
      transform: translateY(-5px); /* Gives it a highly responsive premium lift */
    }

    /* --- 5. MOBILE RESPONSIVENESS TWEAKS --- */
    @media (max-width: 1024px) {
      .button-grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: 20px;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .button-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 15px;
      }
      .pub-button {
        padding: 20px 15px;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        min-height: 80px;
      }
    }
</style>

</BaseLayout>